Package: tlpl
Type: Package
Title: Tau-leaped particle learning
Version: 0.1
Author: Jarad Niemi
Maintainer: Jarad Niemi <niemi@iastate.edu>
Date: 2013-08-13
Description: Tau-leaped particle learning is a sequential Monte Carlo
approach to Bayesian inference in a Poisson-binomial state-space
model, ie. Poisson transitions and binomial observations on those
transitions. Tau-leaping provides a discrete approximation to a 
continuous-time process and particle utilizes analytical tractabilities
of the model to provide an efficient algorithm.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/jarad/tlpl
LazyLoad: yes
Depends:
    stats
Suggests:
    smcUtils,
    testthat
Collate:
    'gillespie.r'
    'Particle.r'
    'pl.step.r'
    'System.r'
    'tlpl_predict.r'
    'tlpl_quantile.r'
    'tlpl.r'
